  "market_context": "NQ 5-minute chart on 9/11/2023 around the New York open. Price formed equal highs near 15430, then consolidated above into a tight range before aggressively sweeping buy-side liquidity into the 15440-15450 area.",
  "key_observation": "After equal highs and consolidation, an aggressive sweep of buy-side liquidity was followed by displacement back into the range, qualifying the upside move as manipulation and setting up distribution lower toward projected standard deviation targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify equal highs near 15430 as a buy-side liquidity pool above the consolidation.",
    "Step 2: Mark the consolidation range that forms above the equal highs as accumulation.",
    "Step 3: Observe the aggressive move sweeping the buy-side liquidity pool to test if it qualifies as manipulation.",
    "Step 4: Confirm manipulation when price shows aggressive displacement back into the range, with a change in state of delivery and market structure shift to the downside.",
    "Step 5: Anchor a standard deviation projection from the manipulation high (around 15450) to the prior low that produced that high, projecting -2 to -2.5 and -4 levels as distribution targets.",
    "Step 6: Plan entries on the change in state of delivery, the bearish order block, or the fair value gap clustered in the same zone, with stop above the manipulation high.",
    "Step 7: Manage the trade by targeting the -2/-2.5 standard deviation first, then watching the order block hold (bodies not closing back through) before continuation to the -4 standard deviation."
  ],
  "outcome": "Entry triggered on the change in state of delivery; price reached the -2 standard deviation target, the bearish order block held on retest (small wick sweep without body closures back through), supporting continuation toward the -4 standard deviation target.",
  "lessons": "Combining AMD with standard deviation projections gives objective distribution targets: project from the manipulation high to its origin low, take entries at the CSD/OB/FVG cluster with stop above the manipulation, and use OB respect to validate continuation to deeper levels.",
